# Day 3 - Array Manipulation

## Definition
Array Manipulation is the process of modifying the existing elements of an array without creating a new array.

## Operations
- Update
- Replace
- Swap
- Shift
- Rotate

## Syntax

### Traverse an Array
```python
for i in range(len(nums)):
```

### Access an Element
```python
nums[i]
```

### Update an Element
```python
nums[i] = new_value
```

### Swap Two Elements
```python
nums[a], nums[b] = nums[b], nums[a]
```

## Algorithm
1. Traverse the array.
2. Check the required condition.
3. Update or swap the element.
4. Print the modified array.

## Time Complexity
- **Time:** O(n)
- **Space:** O(1)

## Common Questions
- Double all elements
- Square all elements
- Replace negative numbers
- Replace even/odd numbers
- Swap first & last element
- Left Shift
- Right Shift
- Rotate Array

## Interview Definition
Array Manipulation is the process of updating, replacing, swapping, shifting, or rotating elements in an array based on the given problem.